txt.en: Dagoras saw a strange figure creeping about in southern Nan Curunír, but soon lost its trail.

'Be wary, [placeholder]. A short while ago, I saw a strange figure moving south towards the pass, but it disappeared before I could determine who or what it might be.\n\n'Stranger still, it left no trail that I could follow. I do not know what became of it.'
Dagoras is at his camp in Nan Curunír.\n\nYou should speak with Dagoras to discover what clues he can offer to help find the strange figure's trail.

'Well, [placeholder], you have my gratitude and then some. It has been a while since I have allowed myself to be caught unaware, and I feel more the fool for it... but I am still alive and that is something, at least.'
'I tried to pick up his trail, but it was well disguised.'
Dagoras is at his camp in Nan Curunír.\n\nYou should speak with Dagoras about the mysterious executioner who attacked him.
'There are not many who can so easily evade my eye. I fear that this individual may have some sinister purpose in mind... we should redouble our efforts to discover what that is.'
Talk to Dagoras at his camp
